Prrojject Manager, UU..NN../lSS.P.P.C.C. . Rhinnocerrooss Beetle Prroojjeecctt*" AAppiia, Western Samoa
The coconut rhinocerooss beetle, (Orycles rhinoceros (L..)))),, is one of about 42 described species of Oryclleess,, the majority of which occur inn Africa. The largest concentration of species iss foundd inn Madagascar andd nearby islands where Paulian (195599)) recorrddeedd 13 species.
The majority of species feedd on palmss as their preferred hosts and several are serious pestss of oil, date,, areca, sago and coconut palms.
O0. rhinocceros is primarily a pest of coconut palmss but a wide range of wildd and cultivated palms is also attacked. Less frequenttllyy,, other crops includdiinngg banana, sugar cane, papayaa andd pineapple are attacked.
Distributioonn
Itt iss generally accepteedd that O0.. rhinnoocceros iss endemic to thee coconut growing regioonnss of Asiaa,, fromm West Pakistan, eastwarddss through India, Ceylonn,, Burma, Hainan, Honngg Kong, Formossaa andd thee Malayyaa Peninsulaa,, thee islandss of Celebes,, Ceraamm andd Amboinaa inn Indonesiaa to thee Philippinnee Islands. (Fig. 1).

