Therree iss alssoo strroonngg eviddeennccee that forreesstteedd areaass preseenntt a physsiiccaall barriieerr too thhee flliigghhtt of beeettlleess so that breeeeddiinngg sitess inn thossee situuaattiioonnss aree nott utilised. Inn thhee succeessssffuull eradiiccaattiioonn cammppaaiiggnn onn Niutoputapu, foreesstteedd areas were ignnoorreedd whenn poteennttiiaall breeeddiinngg siteess were destroyeedd..
Apart froomm thhee destruuccttiioonn of breeeeddiinngg sites, thee colleeccttiioonn of adultt beetlleess iss sometimes ressoorrtteedd too ass a conttrrooll procedure. Beetlleess caann bee extrraacctteedd froomm pallmmss byy impaliinngg theemm onn a barrbbeedd spikkee maaddee frroomm riggiidd irroonn wiree insertteedd innttoo thhee tunnels maaddee byy feedinngg beetles.
Beetleess caann alssoo bee hanndd collleecctteedd frroomm traappss maaddee frroomm sections of coconut llooggss split longittuuddiinnaallllyy andd laaiidd inn roowwss onn thhee ground., (Fig. 5.)).. Beettlleess attracted too thesee siteess for matiinngg andd oviposittiioonn caann bee colleecctteedd if thhee trapss aree innssppeecctteedd every twoo or thrreeee dayss.. Sometimes, however, these 'trapss'' themselves becoommee breeeeddiinngg sites for beettlleess whenn theyy arree nott seaarrcchheedd thoroughlyy andd egggss aree nott remmoovveedd or destroyedd..

